Banco Popular, Grifols, Inditex, Mapfre: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-03-07T05:00:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/banco-popular-grifols-inditex-mapfre-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 index (IBEX)  slipped 0.7 percent to 10,498.70.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  retreated 0.6 percent to 7,902.62.    Banco Popular  SA (POP SM),  Banco de Sabadell SA (SAB)  :
Spain’s domestic lenders may be active after Fitch Ratings
lowered the outlook on AA+ rated Spanish sovereign debt to
“negative.” Popular shares lost 1.2 percent to 4.13 euros.
Sabadell shares fell 0.5 percent to 3.02 euros.    Grifols SA (GRF)  : The U.S. Food and Drug Administration
approved revised labeling for the Spanish pharmaceutical
company’s Alphanate blood-clotting agent to show steps taken to
prevent the compound leading to infections of variant
Creutzfeldt Jakob Disease. The stock gained 0.4 percent to 11.79
euros.    Inditex SA (ITX)  : The Spanish retailer said it bought
the former NBA Store at 666 Fifth Ave. in Manhattan for $324
million, in a record deal for a U.S. retail property. The shares
gained 0.6 percent to 52.27 euros.    Mapfre SA (MAP)  : The Spanish insurer is targeting sales
of 22.5 billion euros ($31.5 billion) this year, compared with
17.2 billion euros in 2010, and is in advance talks with Caja
Madrid over the sale of its stake in a banking joint venture.
The shares rose 0.5 percent to 2.67 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
